{
  "texts": [
    "Our method effectively segments each tooth without erroneously identifying any part of the surface as one of the missing teeth.",
    "In contrast, the other methods falsely segment certain areas of the gum or the 1st molar as the 2 nd molar.",
    "This suggests that the other methods primarily focus on the geometry of the teeth, where the 1 st and 2 nd molars share similarities.",
    "However, considering the surrounding area, it becomes evident that it is the 1 st molar.",
    "The second example represents a common case in which all teeth are present, except the wisdom teeth."
  ]
}